# Mini Text Search Utility

A grep-inspired command-line text search program written in C.

The utility searches standard input or one or more files for lines containing a given pattern. It supports dynamically sized input lines, multiple files, case-insensitive search, inverted matching, line numbering, and match counting.

## Features

- Search one or more text files
- Read input from standard input
- Dynamically process lines of arbitrary length
- Case-insensitive search with `-i`
- Inverted matching with `-v`
- Line numbers with `-n`
- Match counts with `-c`
- Combined options such as `-in` or `-vc`
- File-specific output when searching multiple files
- Defensive handling of allocation and file errors

## Usage

```text
search [options] pattern [file ...]